#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:2
msgid "3270 devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:4
msgid ""
"The 3270 is the classic 'green-screen' console of the mainframes (see the "
"`IBM 3270 Wikipedia article <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM_3270>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:7
msgid ""
"The 3270 data stream is not implemented within QEMU; the device only "
"provides TN3270 (a telnet extension; see `RFC 854 <https://tools.ietf.org/"
"html/rfc854>`__ and `RFC 1576 <https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1576>`__) and "
"leaves the heavy lifting to an external 3270 terminal emulator (such as "
"``x3270``) to make a single 3270 device available to a guest. Note that this "
"supports basic features only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:14
msgid ""
"To provide a 3270 device to a guest, create a ``x-terminal3270`` linked to a "
"``tn3270`` chardev. The guest will see a 3270 channel device. In order to "
"actually be able to use it, attach the ``x3270`` emulator to the chardev."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:19
msgid "Example configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:21
msgid ""
"Make sure that 3270 support is enabled in the guest's Linux kernel. You need "
"``CONFIG_TN3270`` and at least one of ``CONFIG_TN3270_TTY`` (for additional "
"ttys) or ``CONFIG_TN3270_CONSOLE`` (for a 3270 console)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:25
msgid ""
"Add a ``tn3270`` chardev and a ``x-terminal3270`` to the QEMU command line::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:27
msgid ""
"-chardev socket,id=ch0,host=0.0.0.0,port=2300,wait=off,server=on,tn3270=on\n"
"-device x-terminal3270,chardev=ch0,devno=fe.0.000a,id=terminal0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:30
msgid ""
"Start the guest. In the guest, use ``chccwdev -e 0.0.000a`` to enable the "
"device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:33
msgid "On the host, start the ``x3270`` emulator::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:35
msgid "x3270 <host>:2300"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:37
msgid ""
"In the guest, locate the 3270 device node under ``/dev/3270/`` (say, "
"``tty1``) and start a getty on it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:40
msgid "systemctl start serial-getty@3270-tty1.service"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:42
msgid "This should get you an additional tty for logging into the guest."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/s390x/3270.rst:44
msgid ""
"If you want to use the 3270 device as the Linux kernel console instead of an "
"additional tty, you can also append ``conmode=3270 condev=000a`` to the "
"guest's kernel command line. The kernel then should use the 3270 as console "
"after the next boot."
msgstr ""

